# Custom Theme System — T3 Code

## Context

The app currently supports only `"light" | "dark" | "system"` theme modes, applied via `.dark` class on `<html>` and CSS custom properties in `index.css`. There is no concept of named/branded themes and no preview swatches in the settings UI.

This plan adds a typed theme system with 3 built-in themes (`t3-light`, `t3-dark`, `t3-midnight`), persisted to localStorage, applied via a `data-theme` CSS attribute, with a theme selector component showing color swatches in the settings page.

**Constraints:** No new dependencies. No build config changes. Must stay backward-compatible with `DiffWorkerPoolProvider` which consumes `resolvedTheme: "light" | "dark"`.

---

## Approach: `data-theme` Attribute + CSS Blocks

Set `data-theme="<id>"` on `<html>`. Each theme gets a CSS block in `index.css`. The existing `.dark` class + `@variant dark` mechanism is kept intact. The `[data-theme]` attribute selector has higher specificity than `:root`, so it cleanly overrides variables.

---

## Files to Create

### 1. `packages/shared/src/theme.ts` (NEW)

Pure TypeScript, no Effect imports. Define:

```ts
export type ThemeId = "t3-light" | "t3-dark" | "t3-midnight";

// Colors used for swatch previews (plain hex/oklch — not CSS expressions)
export interface ThemeColorSlots {
  background: string;
  foreground: string;
  primary: string;
  sidebar: string;
  editor: string;
  terminal: string;
  statusBar: string;
}

export interface ThemeDefinition {
  id: ThemeId;
  label: string;
  resolvedMode: "light" | "dark";   // drives .dark class toggle
  colors: ThemeColorSlots;           // used by ThemeSelector swatches
}

export const BUILT_IN_THEMES: readonly ThemeDefinition[] = [
  {
    id: "t3-light",
    label: "T3 Light",
    resolvedMode: "light",
    colors: { background: "#ffffff", foreground: "#262626", primary: "#3b5bdb", sidebar: "#f5f5f5", editor: "#ffffff", terminal: "#f9fafb", statusBar: "#e5e7eb" },
  },
  {
    id: "t3-dark",
    label: "T3 Dark",
    resolvedMode: "dark",
    colors: { background: "#0d0d0f", foreground: "#f5f5f5", primary: "#5c7cfa", sidebar: "#111113", editor: "#0d0d0f", terminal: "#0a0a0c", statusBar: "#18181b" },
  },
  {
    id: "t3-midnight",
    label: "T3 Midnight",
    resolvedMode: "dark",
    colors: { background: "#060610", foreground: "#f0f0ff", primary: "#7c6dfa", sidebar: "#0a0a1a", editor: "#060610", terminal: "#04040e", statusBar: "#0f0f22" },
  },
] as const;

export const THEME_IDS = BUILT_IN_THEMES.map((t) => t.id) as ThemeId[];
```

### 2. `apps/web/src/components/ThemeProvider.tsx` (NEW)

Thin root-level wrapper that subscribes `useTheme()` at the top of the tree (ensures DOM stays in sync app-wide):

```tsx
import type { ReactNode } from "react";
import { useTheme } from "../hooks/useTheme";

export function ThemeProvider({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {
  useTheme(); // subscribes to external store; side-effects kept in hook
  return <>{children}</>;
}
```

### 3. `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx` (NEW)

Self-contained. Reads `useTheme()` internally. Renders a "System" option + one card per `BUILT_IN_THEMES` entry.

Each named-theme card shows 4 color swatches (`background`, `primary`, `sidebar`, `editor`) via `style={{ backgroundColor: def.colors[slot] }}` — no dynamic Tailwind classes needed.

Card styling mirrors the existing settings radio-button pattern: `border-primary/60 bg-primary/8` when selected, `border-border bg-background hover:bg-accent` otherwise. Shows a "Selected" badge when active.

---

## Files to Modify

### 4. `packages/shared/package.json`

Add one entry to `exports`:

```json
"./theme": {
  "types": "./src/theme.ts",
  "import": "./src/theme.ts"
}
```

### 5. `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts`

**Type change:**
```ts
// Before
type Theme = "light" | "dark" | "system";
// After
import type { ThemeId } from "@t3tools/shared/theme";
import { BUILT_IN_THEMES, THEME_IDS } from "@t3tools/shared/theme";
type Theme = "system" | ThemeId;
```

**`getStored()` — legacy migration:**
```ts
function getStored(): Theme {
  const raw = localStorage.getItem(STORAGE_KEY);
  if (raw === "system") return "system";
  if ((THEME_IDS as readonly string[]).includes(raw ?? "")) return raw as ThemeId;
  if (raw === "light") return "t3-light";   // migrate old value
  if (raw === "dark") return "t3-dark";     // migrate old value
  return "system";
}
```

**`applyTheme()` — set `data-theme` + keep `.dark` class:**
```ts
function applyTheme(theme: Theme, suppressTransitions = false) {
  if (suppressTransitions) document.documentElement.classList.add("no-transitions");

  const systemDark = getSystemDark();
  const resolvedId: ThemeId =
    theme === "system" ? (systemDark ? "t3-dark" : "t3-light") : theme;

  const def = BUILT_IN_THEMES.find((t) => t.id === resolvedId);
  document.documentElement.classList.toggle("dark", def?.resolvedMode === "dark");
  document.documentElement.setAttribute("data-theme", resolvedId);

  if (suppressTransitions) {
    // oxlint-disable-next-line no-unused-expressions
    document.documentElement.offsetHeight;
    requestAnimationFrame(() => document.documentElement.classList.remove("no-transitions"));
  }
}
```

**`resolvedTheme` derivation** (backward-compatible):
```ts
const resolvedId: ThemeId =
  theme === "system" ? (snapshot.systemDark ? "t3-dark" : "t3-light") : theme;
const def = BUILT_IN_THEMES.find((t) => t.id === resolvedId);
const resolvedTheme: "light" | "dark" = def?.resolvedMode ?? "light";
```

Return shape stays `{ theme, setTheme, resolvedTheme }` — `DiffWorkerPoolProvider` unchanged.

### 6. `apps/web/src/index.css`

Insert after the closing `}` of the `:root { ... }` block (after line ~121). Add three `[data-theme]` blocks:

```css
/* t3-light: :root defaults already express these values */
[data-theme="t3-light"] { /* intentionally empty */ }

/* t3-dark: @variant dark inside :root covers all dark values */
[data-theme="t3-dark"] { /* intentionally empty */ }

/* t3-midnight: deep-black variant overrides both :root and @variant dark */
[data-theme="t3-midnight"] {
  color-scheme: dark;
  --background: oklch(0.095 0.012 264);
  --foreground: var(--color-neutral-50);
  --card: oklch(0.115 0.014 264);
  --card-foreground: var(--color-neutral-50);
  --popover: oklch(0.115 0.014 264);
  --popover-foreground: var(--color-neutral-50);
  --primary: oklch(0.62 0.22 270);
  --primary-foreground: var(--color-white);
  --secondary: --alpha(var(--color-white) / 5%);
  --secondary-foreground: var(--color-neutral-100);
  --muted: --alpha(var(--color-white) / 5%);
  --muted-foreground: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-neutral-400) 90%, var(--color-white));
  --accent: --alpha(var(--color-white) / 5%);
  --accent-foreground: var(--color-neutral-100);
  --destructive: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-red-500) 90%, var(--color-white));
  --border: --alpha(var(--color-white) / 8%);
  --input: --alpha(var(--color-white) / 10%);
  --ring: oklch(0.62 0.22 270);
  --destructive-foreground: var(--color-red-400);
  --info: var(--color-blue-400);
  --info-foreground: var(--color-blue-300);
  --success: var(--color-emerald-400);
  --success-foreground: var(--color-emerald-300);
  --warning: var(--color-amber-400);
  --warning-foreground: var(--color-amber-300);
}
```

**Specificity:** `[data-theme]` = `[0,1,0]` vs. `:root` = `[0,0,1]` — attribute wins. `@variant dark` compiles to `.dark &` which also has `[0,1,0]` but comes before in source order, so the `[data-theme="t3-midnight"]` block (declared later) still wins.

### 7. `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx`

- Remove the `THEME_OPTIONS` constant (lines 25–41)
- Remove `resolvedTheme` from the `useTheme()` destructure (no longer used in this file)
- Remove the entire `<div role="radiogroup">` radio group + "Active theme:" paragraph
- Add: `import { ThemeSelector } from "../components/ThemeSelector";`
- Replace Appearance section body with `<ThemeSelector />`
- Update description text: `"Choose your preferred color theme."`
- Since `ThemeSelector` owns the `useTheme()` call, the `useTheme()` call in `SettingsRouteView` can be removed entirely

### 8. `apps/web/src/routes/__root.tsx`

Wrap `RootRouteView` return with `ThemeProvider`:

```tsx
import { ThemeProvider } from "../components/ThemeProvider";

// Inside RootRouteView:
return (
  <ThemeProvider>
    <ToastProvider>
      <AnchoredToastProvider>
        <EventRouter />
        <DesktopProjectBootstrap />
        <Outlet />
      </AnchoredToastProvider>
    </ToastProvider>
  </ThemeProvider>
);
```

---

## Data Flow Summary

```
User picks "T3 Midnight"
  → setTheme("t3-midnight") → localStorage.setItem("t3code:theme", "t3-midnight")
  → applyTheme("t3-midnight")
    → resolvedId = "t3-midnight", def.resolvedMode = "dark"
    → html.classList.toggle("dark", true)       ← @variant dark activates in :root
    → html.setAttribute("data-theme", "t3-midnight")  ← overrides :root + @variant dark
  → resolvedTheme = "dark"  ← DiffWorkerPoolProvider unchanged
```

---

## Verification

1. **`bun typecheck`** in both `packages/shared` and `apps/web` — confirm `ThemeId`, `useTheme` signatures, and all call sites
2. **`bun lint`** — no new barrel imports; `oxlint-disable` comment preserved
3. **Visual — cold load:** no `localStorage` key → system default → `t3-light` or `t3-dark` per OS
4. **Visual — select "T3 Midnight":** deep black bg, `data-theme="t3-midnight"` on `<html>`, `.dark` class present
5. **Visual — swatches:** 4 colored circles per named theme in settings, correct colors
6. **Visual — system toggle:** switch between system/named themes, diff panel still renders with correct light/dark diff theme
7. **Legacy migration:** set `localStorage["t3code:theme"] = "dark"` manually, reload → resolves to `t3-dark`
8. **Cross-tab sync:** `storage` event fires when changing theme in another tab

